main.java.models

Interface Entity

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Bullet, Enemy, Player, Score

    public interface Entity
    An interface created to allow iterating through all of the updatable entities. Probably some of this stuff should be swapped with an actual class because of similarities in implementation between the different entities. Only the tick() method should stay.
    Author:
    Naichiri

    • Method Detail

      • tick

        void tick(long interval)
        The method called for each entity that changes with time. Most classes implementing Entity interface use interval to move the objects accordingly.
        Parameters:
        interval - time passed since the last time the tick() was called
